{
  "texts": [
    "Teachers are trained to acquire modern pedagogical skills to help students prepare for modern technological societies (Meng et al. 2022; Song and Zhou, 2021).",
    "Another aspect of this shift resulted in repositioning students as central figures in the learning process, helping them in hands-on exploration and collaborative STEM tasks (Zhou and Li, 2021a, 2021b).",
    "A unified framework of STEM integration enables students to weave disparate knowledge strands into a holistic curriculum (Han and Appelbaum, 2018a, 2018b).",
    "Using interconnected knowledge equips them with 21st-century skills, such as practical and innovative abilities to tackle realistic problems and develop a systematic understanding of the world (Han et al. 2020).",
    "However, this paradigm shift has not been without its challenges."
  ]
}